Field Label: END FORM

INSTRUCTIONS: This form is to be completed by the clinician or ADRC staff. The purpose of this form is to record all prescription medications taken by the participant within the two weeks before the current visit. If the participant is receiving any treatments known to significantly impact Alzheimer disease and related dementias (ADRD) biomarkers as part of their clinical care at the time of clinical assessment (e.g., they are receiving aducanumab infusions), the treatment should be included on both this form and the A4a ADRD-Specific Treatments form.

OTC (non-prescription) medications need not be reported; however, a few of these medications are included in the drop-down list of the top 100 drugs. 

For additional clarification and examples, see UDS Coding Guidebook for Form A4.
Is the participant currently taking any medications?

NACC has provided 3 different options for looking up RXNorm drug codes (RXCUIs):

  • RXNorm-validated fields
    • Allows you to look up RXCUIs within REDCap
  • Drop-down list of Top 100 drugs
    • This list aligns with the Form A4: Medications PDF form and allows you to search ingredients or brands within the drop-down menu to select the RXCUI for generic ingredient to enter the NACC database
  • Integer-validated text fields
    • If you are not able (or do not want) to use RXNorm validation within your version of REDCap, you can use the RXNav lookup tool https://mor.nlm.nih.gov/RxNav/ to find the RXCUI and enter the drug code. 
    • We recommend keeping at least a few of these fields so that you can enter "0 = No RXCUI code available" for the rare cases in which an RXCUI is not available in the RXNorm database

Please feel free to keep as many of each option as you prefer for your center. You can report up to 40 drugs per visit per participant and the variables should be named RXNORMID1-RXNORMID-40.
